<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>down to earth • down to the ground</xh5><p> <i>down to earth—</i>pragmatic; realistic: The committee will include some <u>down-to-earth</u> people who know something about what goes on.</p><p><i>down to the ground</i>—(coll.) 1. thoroughly; completely: He looks as if he could be trusted <u>down to the ground</u>. 2. said of smth. that is very typical of a person: He made some rude remarks, but then that’s Bill <u>down to the ground</u>.</p> </entry>
